Done.

I trained LensKit 0.14.4 `ImplicitMF` (ALS) on MovieLens100K from `u.data` with:
- implicit interactions defined as ratings `> 3`
- iterative 5-core filtering on users and items
- 3 random seeds: `1, 2, 3`
- 80/20 user-based holdout splits
- `batch.recommend` used for all evaluation users at once
- default hyperparameters as used in the code: `features=50`, `iterations=20`, `reg=0.1`, `weight=40`

Per-seed results:
- Seed 1: nDCG@10 = 0.2050, Precision@10 = 0.1526
- Seed 2: nDCG@10 = 0.2039, Precision@10 = 0.1486
- Seed 3: nDCG@10 = 0.2010, Precision@10 = 0.1505

Aggregate across seeds:
- Mean nDCG@10 = 0.203309
- Std nDCG@10 = 0.002027
- Mean Precision@10 = 0.150569
- Std Precision@10 = 0.001973

The results CSV was saved to:
`C:\Users\Robin\Documents\GitHub\AutoRecLabTeam5\workspace\working\ml100k_implicitmf_results.csv`
